<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{exterior movie theater 1980's night}
<A>__{a brightly lit marquee reads, "revenge of the nerds." the doors to the theater open and a crowd pours onto the street. harvey, joyce and toby are among them. toby proudly wears a "genuine nerd" button on his striped shirt.}
<C>__{joyce}
<D>__{i agree with toby. i think it's a story of hope and tolerance.}
<C>__{toby}
<D>__{yes. it's about time that the people who get picked on get to be the heroes.}
<A>__{harvey scrunches his face in disbelief.}
<C>__{harvey}
<D>__{it's an entertaining flick an' i can see why you like it toby, but those people on the screen ain't even supposed to be you! they're college students whose parents live in big houses in the suburbs. they're gonna get degrees, get good jobs and stop being nerds.}
<A>__{joyce hits harvey.}
<C>__{joyce}
<D>__{harvey, what did i say about loud talking? use your inside voice.}
